Question Text:
Examine the following show command output on a router configured for dynamic NAT:
"â€” Inside Source
access-list 1 pool examsdigest
pool examsdigest: netmask 255.255.255.240
start 190.1.1.1 end 190.1.1.10
type generic, total addresses 10, allocated 10 (100%), misses 595"
You are responsible to find out why users are not being able to reach the Internet.
Choices:
a. Dynamic NAT can't use Standard ACLs
b. The NAT pool does not have enough entries to fulfill the user's requests
c. The cause is not related to dynamic NAT
d. The command output does not provide any clue to identify the problem
LLM Explanation: The output shows that the NAT pool 'examsdigest' has a total of 10 addresses, all of which have been allocated. The 'misses' counter indicates there have been 595 requests that could not be fulfilled due to lack of available addresses in the pool. This suggests the NAT pool is undersized and does not have enough entries to handle the number of users trying to access the Internet.

Question Text: Log messages may tell you about some events, either critical or not. To help you make sense of the importance of each message, IOS assigns each message a severity level. Which of the following severity level means Warning - Warning condition?
LLM Explanation: Severity level 4 in Cisco IOS log messages indicates a warning condition. The severity levels range from 0 to 7, with 0 being the most severe (emergency) and 7 being the least severe (debugging). Level 4 specifically denotes warning messages, which indicate potential issues or conditions that require attention but do not necessarily impact the functioning of the device.

Question Text: Log messages may tell you about some events, either critical or not. To help you make sense of the importance of each message, IOS assigns each message a severity level. Which of the following severity level means Informational: Informational message only?
LLM Explanation: Severity level 6 corresponds to informational messages in Cisco IOS. These messages are not errors, but rather provide information about system events and status for reference. Severity levels range from 0 to 7, with 0 being the most severe (emergency) and 7 being the least severe (debugging).

Question Text: One of the features of SNMPv3 is called message integrity.
LLM Explanation: Message integrity is one of the key features introduced in SNMPv3. It ensures that SNMP messages have not been altered or corrupted in transit, providing protection against tampering. SNMPv3 uses hash-based message authentication codes (HMAC) to verify the integrity of each message.
URLs: ['CCNA 200-301 Official Cert Guide, Volume 1, Chapter 28: SNMP and Network Management - Cisco Press', 'RFC 3414: User-based Security Model (USM) for version 3 of the Simple Network Management Protocol (SNMPv3) - IETF']

Question Text: You have been tasked to find out whether the Cisco Discovery Protocol (CDP) is enabled globally. Which command will you type?
Choices:
a. show running-config
b. show protocols
c. show cdp
d. show interface brief
LLM Explanation: The 'show cdp' command is used to display information about the Cisco Discovery Protocol (CDP) configuration and status on a Cisco device. This command will show whether CDP is enabled globally on the device, as well as other CDP-related information such as the CDP timer, holdtime, and the interfaces on which CDP is enabled.

Question Text: Which of the following protocols synchronize the time of different systems?
Choices:
a. UDP
b. SMTP
c. CDP
d. NTP
LLM Explanation: NTP (Network Time Protocol) is used to synchronize the clocks of computer systems over packet-switched, variable-latency data networks. It allows network devices to maintain accurate timekeeping by periodically querying NTP servers. The other options are not related to time synchronization: UDP is a transport layer protocol, SMTP is used for email transmission, and CDP is a Cisco proprietary protocol for discovering information about locally attached devices.

Question Text: R1 and R2 are attached to the same Ethernet VLAN, with subnet 192.168.1.0/24, and addresses 192.168.1.1, 192.168.2 respectively. The routers use an FHRP. Host A and host B attach to the same LAN and have correct default router settings per the FHRP configuration. Which of the following statements is true for this LAN?
Choices:
a. If one router fails, both hosts will use the one remaining router as a default router
b. If one router fails, hosts can't send packets off-subnet
c. You can't connect two routers to the same LAN subnet.
d. if one router fails, only one of the two hosts will still be able to send packets off-subnet
LLM Explanation: In a LAN with two routers configured with a First Hop Redundancy Protocol (FHRP) like HSRP or VRRP, if one router fails, the other router will take over as the active router. All hosts on the LAN will then use the remaining router as their default gateway to send packets off-subnet. The FHRP ensures that there is always an active router available to forward traffic, providing redundancy and preventing a single point of failure.
URLs: ['Cisco CCNA 200-301 Official Cert Guide, Chapter 16: First Hop Redundancy Protocol', 'https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/support/docs/ip/hot-standby-router-protocol-hsrp/9234-hsrpguidetoc.html']

Question Text: Which of the following characteristics of network traffic can be managed by Quality of Service (QoS)? (Choose all that apply)
Choices:
a. Jitter
b. CoS
c. Delay
d. LLQ
e. Loss
f. Bandwidth
LLM Explanation: Quality of Service (QoS) is a set of technologies used to manage network traffic and ensure high-quality performance for critical applications. QoS can manage the following characteristics of network traffic:a. Jitter: QoS can minimize jitter, which is the variation in delay of received packets, by ensuring a consistent delay for priority traffic.c. Delay: QoS can prioritize time-sensitive traffic to minimize end-to-end delay and latency.e. Loss: QoS can prevent packet loss for priority traffic by ensuring that high-priority packets are not dropped during network congestion.f. Bandwidth: QoS can allocate and reserve bandwidth for specific applications or traffic types to ensure they have sufficient network resources.The other options, CoS (Class of Service) and LLQ (Low Latency Queuing), are QoS mechanisms or tools rather than characteristics of network traffic.
URLs: ['Cisco Press CCNA 200-301 Official Cert Guide, Chapter 11: Quality of Service (QoS)', 'https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/products/ios-nx-os-software/quality-of-service-qos/index.html']
